  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.12.0`\r\nCL client & version: all\r\nOS & Version: all\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nSending a future TX (`tx_nonce > address_txCount`) to mempool should either be successful or worded with something along the lines \"cannot process future transaction currently\". \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nCurrently, the user gets https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/78f7a6b7f29acd31e16a8ef41e37ae15d515f840/core/txpool/txpool.go#L93\r\n\r\nwith poor wording: `\"future transaction tries to replace pending\"` - even though there is no pending TX of that address in the pool.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSend a future TX to the node when the pool is in it's global limit.\r\n",
